INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (168, 2, '2011-07-13 01:18:41', '2011-07-13 09:18:41', '<a href="http://www.avishek.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/composite_som_big2.gif"><img src="http://www.avishek.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/som39.jpg" alt="SOM Evolution" title="composite_som_big" width="300" height="300" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-196" /></a>\r\n(Click the image to see the evolution of the SOM)\r\n\r\nThe image above was generated off 200 samples of a large data set. Sample vectors were 56-dimensional bit strings. The similarity measure used was the Hamming Distance. Brighter green represents values at a higher Hamming Distance with respect to zero.\r\nThe (very dirty) code is up at Github <a href="https://github.com/asengupta/Self-Organising-Map">here</a>.\r\nUnrelated: I\'ve been watching <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H1Zbp6__uNw">Leonard Susskind\'s lectures on Statistical Mechanics</a>; they\'re a <em>tour de force</em>.', 'Playing around with Self Organising Maps', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'playing-around-with-self-organising-maps', '', '', '2011-07-13 13:18:25', '2011-07-13 21:18:25', '', 0, 'http://www.avishek.net/blog/?p=168', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
